Which of the following best describes the difference between the DROP and REJECT targetsin iptables?
A)  Both DROP and REJECT do the same thing.
B)  DROP silently discards packets, while REJECT sends back an ICMP acknowledgment.
C)  REJECT silently discards packets, while DROP sends back an ICMP acknowledgment.
D)  DROP sends back a direct message, and REJECT sends a redirect.
B
B. The DROP target silently discards packets that match the rule. An ICMP unreachable mes-sage is sent back for REJECT. In general, DROP is preferred in order to reduce the chances ofdenial of service (DoS) or other information- gathering issues.
